  "body": "# Problem\r\nBoth iOS and Android Status app currently includes the ability to grab screenshots. On Android this ability is disabled by default, but an option is provided to enable. On iOS there is no setting to enable/disable screenshots (only 'Hide previews' when moving between apps).\r\n\r\nThere is always the option to grab another phone or a Nightly or Develop build. However, the option to enable screenshots on Android and the ability to grab screenshots on iOS increases the threat for message senders.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n- Design input needed to prompt a dialog when a screenshot is attempted\r\n- iOS needs further investigation. Supposedly blocking screenshots is not possible on iOS. An alternative could be to detect, warn and possibly hide the screen the user is attempting to take a screenshot of. \r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n- Screenshots and recordings are disabled on Android Play store/App store release\r\n- No option is provided in settings to enable Screenshots (and/or recordings) on Android Play store/App store release\r\n\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\nScreenshots should be possible in PR and Nightly builds for development purposes. See #11323 \r\n\r\n",
