    "body": "I'd appreciate it if the option (on android) was left as is. \nIf I want to take screenshots of my passwords, my banking info, or even to take pictures of private areas or whatever I may choose. We should be allowed to assume the risk. \n\nPerhaps \nA) provide a warning when enabling screenshots\nB) relocate the toggle to advanced options \nC) leave it there for PR, nightly AND f-droid builds as well. \n\nOr\n\nIs it possible to \"allow others to screenshot chats\" where, if \n1. USER A = disabled and USER B = enabled\n2. USER B opens chat with USER A\n3. The action of tapping to enter the chat with USER A would automatically switch the screenshot state for USER B from enabled > disabled.\n4. Exiting the chat would revert the change.\n\nThe action to change state should only effect users who have manually enabled screenshots.  \n\n2b. For group chats, ~~if any one member has screenshots disabled, screenshots are disabled for all users when the conversation is in the foreground. ~~\n\nFor group and community chats, the admin should set this.\n\nBasically, tapping to open the chat would \"set screenshot toggle to off\" (if previously on).\nBacking out of the chat would revert to previous manually set setting. \n\nCheers\nüçª ",
